{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/2/comments/51878041.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake:d8d5f9990288..87cfed357da4?path=cmake%2FIgnImportTarget.cmake"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/2/_/diff#comment-51878041"}}, "parent": {"id": 51877917, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/2/comments/51877917.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/2/_/diff#comment-51877917"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 2, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pullrequests/2.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-cmake/pull-requests/2"}}, "title": "Creating project components [Ready For Review]"}, "content": {"raw": "Yeah, I'm creating a separate fix for this that will target `default` in its own PR.\n\nI've found a discussion on the issue: https://cmake.org/Bug/view.php?id=13462\n\nIt seems the correct approach (until `target_include_directories(~)` works) is to use `set_property(~)` instead of `set_target_properties(~)`. Kind of a goofy idiosyncrasy, but so be it.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Yeah, I'm creating a separate fix for this that will target <code>default</code> in its own PR.</p>\n<p>I've found a discussion on the issue: <a href=\"https://cmake.org/Bug/view.php?id=13462\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">https://cmake.org/Bug/view.php?id=13462</a></p>\n<p>It seems the correct approach (until <code>target_include_directories(~)</code> works) is to use <code>set_property(~)</code> instead of <code>set_target_properties(~)</code>. Kind of a goofy idiosyncrasy, but so be it.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-12-13T20:53:54.324894+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Grey", "uuid": "{c1cdfe52-2887-474c-ae99-72fdc53a59c